OL,6,FHotel stays can become wearing when
OL,7,Fthey go on for too long since, for
OL,8,Fmost people, there's no place like
OL,9,Fhome. But a retired lawyer in Italy
OL,10,Fis proving that the opposite can be
OL,11,Fthe case.
OL,13,FSergio Cappelli, 65, has been living
OL,14,Fin a hotel in his native city of
OL,15,FNaples for the past seven years, ever
OL,16,Fsince he decided to get rid of his
OL,17,Ffamily home.
OL,3,C'I saved money by giving up my house
OL,4,Cto live permanently in a hotel'
